1 Section 1. NRS 703.196 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 703.196 1. Any books, accounts, records, minutes, papers
3 and property of any public utility, alternative seller, provider of
4 discretionary natural gas service or provider of new electric
5 resources that are subject to examination pursuant to NRS 703.190
6 or 703.195 and are made available to the Commission, any officer or
7 employee of the Commission, an affected governmental entity, any
8 officer or employee of an affected governmental entity, the Bureau
9 of Consumer Protection in the Office of the Attorney General or any
10 other person under the condition that the disclosure of such
11 information to the public be withheld or otherwise limited, must not
12 be disclosed to the public unless the Commission first determines
13 that the disclosure is justified.
14 2. The Commission shall take such actions as are necessary to
15 protect the confidentiality of such information, including, without
16 limitation:
17 (a) Granting such protective orders as it deems necessary; and
18 (b) Holding closed hearings to receive or examine such
19 information.
20 3. If the Commission closes a hearing to receive or examine
21 such information, it shall:
22 (a) Restrict access to the records and transcripts of such hearings
23 without the prior approval of the Commission or an order of a court
24 of competent jurisdiction authorizing access to the records or
25 transcripts; and
26 (b) Prohibit any participant at such a hearing from disclosing
27 such information without the prior authorization of the Commission.
28 4. A representative of the Regulatory Operations Staff of the
29 Commission and the Bureau of Consumer Protection:
30 (a) May attend any closed hearing held pursuant to this section;
31 and
32 (b) Have access to any records or other information determined
33 to be confidential pursuant to this section.
